decades, American Democrats have been in some ways similar to the democratic socialist parties of Europe, while recent Republicans are ideologically similar to Britain's Conservatives. However, it's easy to exaggerate the similarities, given the influence of local conditions, and both major American parties have been undergoing changes recently. <br><br><LI><strong>Parents frustrated by Illinois school strike</strong> (Monday, 11/4/96)<br>The Niles Township school strike goes on. <A HREF="http://www.suntimes.com/news/newsitems/NILES_Nov04.html">Here's the latest</A> from the <b>Chicago Sun-Times</b>. <br><br><LI><strong>Hong Kong professor says government reluctant to recognize poverty</strong> (Monday, 11/4/96)<br><A HREF="http://www.hkstandard.com/online/news/001/hongkong/news010.htm">Recognizing that poverty exists</A> in Hong Kong would have budgetary implications, according to Professor Stewart MacPherson. Today's <b>Hong Kong Standard</b> has this story, as well as one about <A HREF="http://www.hkstandard.com/online/news/001/hongkong/news014.htm">employment opportunities for Filipino maids</A> following the handover of the British colony to China next year. <br><br><LI><strong>Temporary shutdown of Seagate plant won't result in layoffs</strong> (Monday, 11/4/96)<br>A new Seagate Technology plant in Singapore will shut down temporarily for technical reasons, but workers will be <A HREF="http://www.asia1.com.sg/biztimes/pages/nsing03.html">temporarily reassigned</A>, according to the <b>Singapore Business Times</b>. <br><br><LI><strong>Indiana strike ended</strong> (Sunday, 11/3/96)<br>One of the local strikes has ended following the tentative national agreement between the United Auto Workers and General Motors. Here's the story from <A HREF="http://www.yahoo.com/headlines/961103/news/stories/gm_39.html">Reuters</A> and the <A HREF="http://www.nytimes.com/yr/mo/day/news/financial/gm-labor.html">New York Times</A>. <br><br><LI><strong>How far will African crisis