<html><head><title>Dr. Jerry Willenbring</title></head></HEAD><BODY vlink="#FF0000"><P>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff"><H3><CENTER>Life and Work in the Revolutionary New World Economy</CENTER><center></H2><P><IMG src="LOGO.GIF" alt="[Gary Johnson's BraveNewWorkWorld.All about work all the time. For business, education, and careers.]"></center><b><center><strong><FONT SIZE=-1><A HREF="default.html">HOME PAGE</A> | <A HREF="Today's_news.html">NewWork News</A> | <A HREF="Guest_commentary.html">Guest Commentary</A> | <A HREF="NewWork_reviews.html">Reviews</A> | <A HREF="Tech_watch.html">Tech Watch</A><br><A HREF="Ed_watch.html">Ed Watch</A> |<A HREF="Resources.html">Resources</A> | <A HREF ="Archives.html">Archives</A> | <A HREF ="Feedback.html">Feedback</A></FONT></strong></center></b><br><p><p><p><p><center><strong><h1>Introducing</h1></center><p><center><img src="Jerry.GIF"</center><p><center>Dr. Jerry Willenbring<br> Chief Executive Officer<br>The New Work Corporation</strong></center></center><p><p><center>E-mail: jerry@newwork.com</center><p><p><p>Jerry Willenbring has had long and varied professional experience and brings a broad perspective to work in the revolutionary new world economy. He has had extensive experience as a research scientist, engineer, entrepreneur, executive, consultant, and educator. <p>Jerry spent more than twenty years on the cutting edge of high-technology research and development. He has played key technical and management roles in the development of new processes, products, and companies, as well as innovative consortial programs and strategic alliances across business, academe, and government. He has had extensive team building, entrepreneurial, strategic planning, and business planning experience. He has also worked to assist others in the development of their full creative potential for success in a radically reorganized economic context. For example, in addition to everything else, Jerry is a Licensed Career Counselor in the State of Texas.<p>In addition to post-graduate training in business and management, Jerry holds B.S., M.S., and Ph.D. degrees in electrical engineering from the University of Minnesota. During the mid-1970's, he did post-doctoral work at the Max Planck Institute for Biophysical Chemistry in West Germany, and, then, served on the faculty of the Free University of Berlin, where the great physicist, Werner Heisenberg, had worked years earlier. He has also taught and helped in the development of electrical engineering curricula in the Minnesota State University system.<p>Jerry worked as a Senior Principal Research Scientist at the Honeywell Systems and Research Center in Minneapolis for several years, where he acted as manager of several projects involving laser radar, laser remote sensing and commercialization of gas laser technologies.<p>Jerry served as Senior Principal Design Engineer for Rosemount, Inc. in Minneapolis, where he was responsible for strategic planning, technology assessment, technical evaluation of acquisition and licensing candidates and monitoring of contract research in fiberoptic sensors and laser remote sensing. Following this, he served as Senior Consultant at Control Data Corporation, where he was responsible for strategic planning in optoelectronics and fiber optic interconnects and also organized and conducted various seminars and professional conferences. <p>In 1989, Jerry went to work as Program Manager of the Optics in Computing Program, at Microelectronics and Computer Technology Corporation (MCC) in Austin, Texas, a research and technology consortium organized by Bobby Inman. He formed and managed a large program for commercialization of holographic data storage, involving the U.S. Department of Commerce's Advanced Technology Program, MCC, and several large corporations. He also served as Director of High End Products for Tamarack Storage Devices, a spin-off company formed to develop and manufacture holographic storage products. <p>During the 1980's, Jerry was founder and CEO of Minnesota Laser Corporation. More recently, he founded <a name= "careers"</a><A HREF="http://www.colinc.com/">Careers Online, Inc.</A>, an innovative recruitment firm specializing in personnel with expertise in leading-edge computer software technologies and applications, worldwide.<p>During recent years, Jerry has become increasingly concerned with broader issues relating to life and work in the revolutionary new world economy, including the implications of historic changes for individual well-being, family relationships, and education. For instance, rather than focusing on technology itself from now on, Jerry will concern himself with the personal and social <em>implications</em> of technology. Like his equal partner, Gary Johnson, Jerry has had extensive international experience and tries to maintain a global perspective on work, education, and most other things.<p>Dr. Jerry Willenbring is Chief Executive Officer and co-founder of The New Work Corporation. In addition to his executive responsibilities in guiding our company, Jerry will make media appearances, spend considerable time writing, and conduct seminars on life and work in the revolutionary new world economy for individuals, business, and education.<p>Now, go to an introduction to Jerry's equal partner, <A HREF="Gary.html">Gary Johnson</A><p><p><p><p><p><center><hr width=200; size=5><FONT SIZE=+1><A HREF="default.html"><b>Return to top of home page</strong></A><p><FONT SIZE=+1><strong><A HREF="Today's_news.html">NewWork News</A> | <A HREF="Guest_commentary.html">Guest Commentary</A> | <A HREF="NewWork_reviews.html">Reviews</A> |<A HREF="Tech_watch.html">Tech Watch</A><br><A HREF="Ed_watch.html">Ed Watch</A> |<A HREF="Resources.html">Resources</A> | <A HREF ="Archives.html">Archives</A> | <A HREF ="Feedback.html">Feedback</A></FONT></strong></center><center><hr width=200; size=5></center><p><p><center><img src="LogoB.GIF" alt="[BraveNewWorkWorld and NewWork News are at http://www.newwork.com. All about work. All the time. For business, education, and careers.]"></center><p><p><p><p><p><P><HR><STRONG><FONT SIZE=-1>Copyright &copy; 1996 Gary Johnson Communications.All rights reserved. BraveNewWorkWorld, NewWork, and Women in the New Economy are trademarks of Gary Johnson Communications.</FONT></STRONG></BODY></HTML>
