<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>CRFD-Simulation of Combustion Processes in Diesel Engines</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY Background="http://troja.ethz.ch/Seiten_Ausstattung/Hintergrund.GIF" >
<A
<A HREF="http://troja.ethz.ch/Publik/Projects/index.html"><IMG
SRC="http://troja.ethz.ch/Seiten_Ausstattung/Balken-UP.GIF" ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=100%
BORDER=0  ALT="IET/LVV ETHZ UP"></A>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=5>CRFD-Simulation of Combustion Processes in Diesel Engines</FONT>
<P> 
<HR WIDTH=100%  ALIGN=CENTER SIZE=4>
<P>
<B>
Summary:
</B>
<P>
Environmental considerations and the associated demand for pollution 
control have become an important issue in the design of almost all 
combustion machines. For direct injection diesel engines the formation 
of pollutants  like soot, nitric oxides and unburned hydrocarbons are 
determined by the nature of the fuel spray. Computational Reactive 
Fluid Dynamics (CRFD) is a powerful and flexible tool for the 
investigation of the fundamental processes which govern the spray and 
combustion phenomena in reciprocating engines.
<P>
The objective of this project is the closer coordination of the 
research efforts between universities and industries through 
complementary developments, exchange of know-how and the transfer of 
technologies. In particular, the integration of CRFD codes in the 
design process of engines plays an important part in this common 
effort, which in turn requires the improvement of the present models 
and the development of new computational methods and techniques. 
<P>
Contacts:
