<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Low-NOx-Concepts for Natural Gas Fuelled Combustion Engines</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY Background="http://troja.ethz.ch/Seiten_Ausstattung/Hintergrund.GIF" >
<A
<A HREF="http://troja.ethz.ch/Publik/Projects/index.html"><IMG
SRC="http://troja.ethz.ch/Seiten_Ausstattung/Balken-UP.GIF" ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=100%
BORDER=0  ALT="IET/LVV ETHZ UP"></A>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=5>Low-NOx-Concepts for Natural Gas Fuelled Combustion Engines</FONT>
<P> 
<HR WIDTH=100%  ALIGN=CENTER SIZE=4>
<P>
<B>
Summary:
</B>
<P>
Natural gas fuelled combustion engines have the potential to combine low exhaust gas emissions with high power output and good efficiency. In order to meet future stringent emission standards however, further research and development work for gas engines has to be done. Especially the increasing utilisation of gas-fired co-generation has highlighted a keen demand for detailed investigation of the emission level and of the performance of gas engines.
<P>
With regard to lowest exhaust gas emission levels (especially NOx), premixed combustion of gaseous fuels (lean-burn or stoechiometric operation with a three-way-catalyst) is very promising. In close collaboration with engine-manufacturers, research work is carried out at the I. C. Engines and Combustion Laboratory at ETH, in order to investigate several concepts for premixed combustion of gaseous fuels (lean-burn, stoechiometric operation with exhaust gas recirculation) in terms of emissions, power output and efficiency. 
<P>
Contacts:
<P>
A. Zbiorczyk, Dr. K. Boulouchos
<P>
Electronic Contacts:
<P>
<A HREF="mailto:
zbiorczyk@lvv.iet.mavt.ethz.ch">zbiorczyk@lvv.iet.mavt.ethz.ch</A>
<P>
<A HREF="mailto:
boulouchos@lvv.iet.mavt.ethz.ch">boulouchos@lvv.iet.mavt.ethz.ch</A>
<P>

Index Terms:
<P>
