<HEAD>
<TITLE>Experimental Investigation of Turbulence Parameters in the Combustion Chamber of an I.C. Engine with Laser Doppler Velocimetry (LDV)</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY Background="http://troja.ethz.ch/Seiten_Ausstattung/Hintergrund.GIF" >
<A HREF="http://troja.ethz.ch/Publik/Projects/index.html"><IMG  SRC="http://troja.ethz.ch/Seiten_Ausstattung/Balken-UP.GIF" ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=100% BORDER=0  ALT="IET/LVV ETHZ UP"></A>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=5>Experimental Investigation of Turbulence Parameters in the Combustion Chamber of an I.C. Engine with Laser Doppler Velocimetry (LDV)</FONT>
<P>
<HR WIDTH=100%  ALIGN=CENTER SIZE=3>
<P>
<B>
Summary:
</B>
<P>
Combustion in I.C. engines is driven by the complex interaction between fluid mechanics and reaction kinetics. Thus, understanding the evolution of the turbulent flow field prior to combustion is of crucial importance for proper engine design with respect  to thermal efficiency and pollutant formation.
<P>
This research project uses a 3-D fiberoptic LDV system. Investigations carried out under cold flow conditions with a flat piston and a pancake combustion chamber provided information about the mean flow, the turbulence intensities, the integral time scales and the integral length scales of the turbulence field derived by using the Taylor Hypothesis at various locations in the cylinder, at various engine speeds and using different inlet channel configurations in  order to generate different swirl patterns during the intake stroke. Of particular interest are in this context the Reynolds-stresses derived from 3-D simultaneous measurements, the flow field during flame kernel development and in the long term turbulence enhancement during the last stages of combustion.
<P>
Contacts:
<P>
P. Dimopoulos, K. Boulouchos
<P>
Electronic Contacts:
<P>
<A HREF="mailto:dimopoulos@lvv.iet.mavt.ethz.ch">dimopoulos@lvv.iet.mavt.ethz.ch</A>  
<P>
Index Terms:
<P>
Engine Fluid Dynamics<BR>
Laser Doppler Velocimetry<BR>
Turbulence<BR>
Reynolds Stresses
<P>
Supported By:
<P>
Swiss Federal Office of Energy (BEW) Grant Number EF-FOS (88)6.
<P>
<A HREF="http://troja.ethz.ch"><IMG  SRC="http://troja.ethz.ch/Seiten_Ausstattung/Home_Public.GIF" ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=33% BORDER=0  ALT="Home Page Public"></A>
<A HREF="http://troja.ethz.ch/Intern/Erste_Seite_Intern.html"><IMG  SRC="http://troja.ethz.ch/Seiten_Ausstattung/Home_Intern.GIF" ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=33% BORDER=0  ALT="Home Page Intern"></A>
