<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Laseroptical Diagnostic Method for Fuel Spray Visualization in a DI Diesel Engine</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY Background="http://troja.ethz.ch/Seiten_Ausstattung/Hintergrund.GIF" >
<A HREF="http://troja.ethz.ch/Publik/Projects/index.html"><IMG  SRC="http://troja.ethz.ch/Seiten_Ausstattung/Balken-UP.GIF" ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=100% BORDER=0  ALT="IET/LVV ETHZ UP"></A>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=5>Laseroptical Diagnostic Method for Fuel Spray Visualization in a DI Diesel Engine</FONT>
<P>
<HR WIDTH=100%  ALIGN=CENTER SIZE=3>
<B>Summary:
</B>
<P>
Modern electronic engine control systems provide a great deal of control parameters in order to meet both the emissions standards at a reasonable fuel consumption and the necessity of good overall operation at all possible engine conditions. In a former project (Hybrid IIB) optimizations were done on a DI diesel engine with an Electronic Common Rail injection system (ECR) and controlled Exhaust Gas Recirculation (EGR). However, more detailed information of the fuel/air-distribution and the precise structure  of fuel sprays is required.
<P>
In order to investigate and optimize the injection process a new
non-instrusive, optical diagnostic tool is being developed. The envisaged technique is capable to determine the structure of high velocity dense fuel sprays in engines, operating at practical  conditions. In this context injection related values like spray propagation, droplet size and droplet density distribution will be examined. First experiments were done to determine the visibility of the spray and the combustion as a function of the overall operation time, and the engine operating state. The results show no serious restriction of the optical access to the combustion chamber due to soot deposition on the sapphire window at the measured operating states.
<P>
Contacts:
<P>
M. St&ouml;ckli, B. Ineichen
<P>
Electronic Contacts:
<P>
<A HREF="mailto:"stoeckli@lvv.iet.mavt.ethz.ch>stoeckli@lvv.iet.mavt.ethz.ch</A>
<P>
Index Terms:
<P>
Fuel Spray Visualization<BR>
Speckle Sheet Diagnostics<BR>
Common Rail Injection System
<P>
 Supported By:
<P>
