<HEAD>
<TITLE>Numerical Simulation of Flow and Combustion in a Reciprocating Engine</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY Background="http://troja.ethz.ch/Seiten_Ausstattung/Hintergrund.GIF" >
<A HREF="http://troja.ethz.ch/Publik/Projects/index.html"><IMG  SRC="http://troja.ethz.ch/Seiten_Ausstattung/Balken-UP.GIF" ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=100% BORDER=0  ALT="IET/LVV ETHZ UP"></A>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=5>Numerical Simulation of Flow and Combustion in a Reciprocating Engine</FONT>
<P>
<HR WIDTH=100%  ALIGN=CENTER SIZE=3>
<P>
<B>
Summary:
</B>

<P>
The modeling of combustion and pollutant formation in an internal combustion engine is a challenging task, involving turbulence, transfer processes, spray penetration, chemical kinetics and flame propagation, as well as numerical methods. The level and structure of turbulence in the flow field immediately prior to and shortly after ignition strongly affects combustion and flame propagation. Engine turbulence (both in experiments and computations) is usually characterized for the flow field without combustion (&quot;cold-flow studies&quot;). In the present project we study turbulence parameters in reciprocating engine flows, using numerical solution of the governing  differential equations of compressible flow and appropriate turbulence modeling. The solution is based on the EPISO algorithm and the use of the KIVA-II code. The simulations complement LDA measurements, performed in our Laboratory. Our results for flat and bowl-in-piston geometries yield interesting insights into the characteristics of the turbulent flow field and are in good agreement with experiments. Next steps will involve modeling of flame propagation during premixed combustion and of heat release rate during diffusion combustion.
<P>
Contacts:
<P>
L. Kaiktsis, C. Frouzakis, K. Boulouchos
<P>
Electronic Contacts:
<P>
<A HREF="mailto:"kaiktsis@lvv.iet.mavt.ethz.ch>kaiktsis@lvv.iet.mavt.ethz.ch</A>
<P>
Index Terms:
<P>
Turbulent Flows<BR>
Turbulence Structure in Engines<BR>
Computational Fluid Dynamics
<P>
Supported By:
<P>
Swiss Federal Office of Energy (BEW), Grant Number EF-FOS (88)6.
<P>
<A HREF="http://troja.ethz.ch"><IMG  SRC="http://troja.ethz.ch/Seiten_Ausstattung/Home_Public.GIF" ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=33% BORDER=0  ALT="Home Page Public"></A>
<A HREF="http://troja.ethz.ch/Intern/Erste_Seite_Intern.html"><IMG  SRC="http://troja.ethz.ch/Seiten_Ausstattung/Home_Intern.GIF" ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=33% BORDER=0  ALT="Home Page Intern"></A>
