<HEAD>
<TITLE>Novel Load Control System for IC-Engines</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY Background="http://troja.ethz.ch/Seiten_Ausstattung/Hintergrund.GIF" >
<A HREF="http://troja.ethz.ch/Publik/Projects/X0007_Load_Control/X0007_Load_Control.html"><IMG  SRC="http://troja.ethz.ch/Seiten_Ausstattung/Balken-UP.GIF" ALIGN=TOP BORDER=0  ALT="IET/LVV ETHZ UP"></A>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=5>Optimization of Part Load Performance of S.I. Engines Using Secondary Inlet Valves</FONT>
<P>
<HR WIDTH=100%  ALIGN=CENTER SIZE=3>
<P>
Figure 2:
<P>
<IMG SRC="http://troja.ethz.ch/Publik/Projects/X0007_Load_Control/FIG-2.GIF">
<P>
<FONT SIZE=3>
Extrapolation to fractional power savings possible in a firing engine. The upper curve is made with the assumption that the manifold pressure is kept constant during the inductionstroke, as is more nearly the case for a multicylinder engine.
</FONT>
