<HEAD>
<TITLE>
About Backpacker Accommodation Ratings Guide
</TITLE>
</HEAD> 
<BODY background="background.GIF" link="#236B8E" vlink="#8E234B"</BODY> 

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>About the <br>Backpacker Accommodation<BR>
 Ratings Guide</H1>
<!-- Graphic Tag -->
<CENTER><IMG  SRC="bus.GIF"></CENTER>
<!-- Horizontal Line Tag -->
<HR ALIGN=Center>

<P>
<P>Australia offers a variety of accommodation establishments for budget 
travellers. This guide aims to help you choose accommodation that best 
meets your needs while providing an assurance that certain standards have 
been met by a particular property. 
<P>The Backpacker Accommodation Classification Scheme was introduced in 
1995 by the Australian Automobile Association (AAA) with funding provided 
by the Commonwealth Department of Tourism. The scheme provides an 
independent assessment of accommodation properties based on the voluntary 
participation of industry members. The majority of backpacker 
accommodation establishments in Australia are taking part in the scheme.
<P>Backpacker accommodation is defined for this purpose as properties 
offering, at low cost, a range of sleeping arrangements, including 
dormitories, with communal and self-catering facilities and an emphasis 
on guest interaction. Establishments were rated under guidelines that 
were cooperatively determined between the backpacker industry and the 
AAA. 
<P>This scheme is broadly similar to the 'star' rating schemes for hotels 
and motels, and is based on a rating system of one to five backpacks. One 
backpack denotes an establishment offering clean, simple and basic 
facilities, while at the other end of the scale, five backpacks indicates 
a superior standard of facilities. To qualify for inclusion in the 
scheme, properties must be clean and well maintained. Each establishment 
must also satisfy building, health, fire safety and local council 
regulations. 
<P>Ratings are based on a points system with points being allocated in 
two categories, vital and desirable, based on the guidelines. Vital 
points are critical in determining the one- to five-backpack rating and 
are awarded for those items properties should possess. These include 
minimum facilities in sleeping, bathroom, communal and kitchen areas as 
well as appropriate security features and information sources. Desirable 
points are awarded for many of the optional elements properties may offer 
for the benefit of guests including tour booking services, an extensive 
range of leisure facilities, and additional security and room features. 
<P>The requirements of lower classifications are automatically included 
in higher classifications. 
<P><IMG SRC="./backpack.GIF" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><p>
Vital: 160-259<BR>
Desirable: 0-59<BR>
Clean basic accommodation. 
<P><IMG SRC="./backpack.GIF" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><IMG SRC="./backpack.GIF" 
ALIGN="BOTTOM"><p>
Vital: 260-309<BR>
Desirable: 60-79<BR>
Well maintained establishments offering an average standard of 
accommodation. 
<P><IMG SRC="./backpack.GIF" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><IMG SRC="./backpack.GIF" 
ALIGN="BOTTOM"><IMG SRC="./backpack.GIF" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><p>
Vital: 310-359<BR>
Desirable: 80-94<BR>
Good comfortable accommodation. 
<P><IMG SRC="./backpack.GIF" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><IMG SRC="./backpack.GIF" 
ALIGN="BOTTOM"><IMG SRC="./backpack.GIF" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><IMG 
SRC="./backpack.GIF" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><p>
Vital: 360-399<BR>
Desirable: 95-119<BR>
Very good accommodation offering a high standard of comfort. 
<P><IMG SRC="./backpack.GIF" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><IMG SRC="./backpack.GIF" 
ALIGN="BOTTOM"><IMG SRC="./backpack.GIF" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><IMG 
SRC="./backpack.GIF" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><IMG SRC="./backpack.GIF" 
ALIGN="BOTTOM"><p>
Vital: 400-440<BR>
Desirable: 120-140<BR>
Excellent quality of accommodation. 
<P>The information in this guide is not intended to provide comprehensive 
details about all of an establishment's facilities or to indicate 
anything about its atmosphere or ambience. Where additional facilities 
such as swimming pools and transportation are provided as part of an 
accommodation package, these have not been assessed under this ratings 
system. Other guidebooks provide more comprehensive information on these 
features. 
<P>We hope that this ratings guide will help you to make the right choice 
about the style of hostel accommodation you are looking for and will 
enhance the quality and enjoyment of your travels around Australia. Happy 
hostelling!<p>
<!-- Graphic Tag -->
<IMG WIDTH=90 HEIGHT=113 HSPACE=10 ALT="backpackers accommodation 
classification logo"ALIGN=left SRC="baclogo.GIF">
<i>Look for this symbol on participating hostels.</i><BR clear=all>

<H2>
Disclaimer
</H2>
<P>The Commonwealth as represented by the Department of Tourism has, on 
the basis of information provided to it by the Australian Automobile 
Association ('AAA'), prepared this publication.
 The Commonwealth understands from AAA that the information was that made 
available to AAA from its State and Territory affiliates on or about June 
1995. 
<P>The information set out in the publication is for the guidance only of 
persons who should satisfy themselves by inspection or otherwise as to 
whether the accommodation would be appropriate in their particular case. 

<P>The information is provided gratuitously and the Commonwealth, AAA and 
the State and Territory affiliates of AAA, whether jointly or severally:
<P>(a) do not accept responsibility; and
<P>(b) disclaim any liability
<P>for any personal injury, death, or in the case of loss or damage to 
persons using, owning or providing accommodation, service or product, 
sustained by reason of any accommodation, service or product chosen or 
not chosen in reliance on information in this publication.
