<HEAD>
<TITLE>Natsitis projects</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY background="background.GIF" link="#42426f" vlink="#8e2323"</BODY> 
<!-- Graphic Tag -->
<IMG WIDTH=453 HEIGHT=18 ALT="Number 9, September 1995" 
SRC="issuenumbergold.GIF"></P><H1>
Natsitis pilot projects selected
</H1>
<!-- Graphic Tag -->
<IMG WIDTH=266 HEIGHT=144 hspace=10 BORDER=1 ALT="Karijini Visitor 
Centre"ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="karijini.GIF"><CITE>
Hancock Gorge, Karijini National Park, Pilbara Region, WA. Funding will 
help the Karijini Aboriginal
 Corporation to produce top quality publications and interpretive 
displays for the Karijini Visitor Centre. (Photo
 courtesy of Norm Nickerson, Last Frontier, WA)
</CITE><P>The March issue of <I>Talking Tourism</I> reported that a draft 
National Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Tourism
 Industry Strategy had been released for public comment. The strategy 
aims to increase the number of indigenous
 people employed in the tourism industry.
<P>The stategy was developed by the Tourism Industry Advisory Committee 
(TIAC), a body comprising representives
 from the Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Commission (ATSIC), the 
Department of Tourism, other government
 agencies, tourism industry bodies, and Aboriginal and Torres Strait 
Islander tourism operators. It aims to increase the
 number of indigenous people employed in the tourism industry.
<P><I>Talking Tourism</I> also reported that the ATSIC had called for 
applications for funding for pilot projects to test some of
 the key elements of the draft strategy. 
<P>Based on recommendations from TIAC, 12 projects have now been selected 
to receive grants totalling <NOBR>$690 850:</NOBR>
<!-- List Tag -->
<UL>
<LI><B>Gringai Aboriginal Culture Tours</B> to establish cultural tours 
in the Hunter region.<P>
<LI><B>Koori Aboriginal Cultural Tours</B> for a tourism feasibility 
study involving 25 communities in New South Wales.<P>
<LI><B>Ngurratjuta/Pmara Ntjarra</B> for a tourism unit to help existing 
and potential indigenous tourism enterprises in the Alice Springs area, 
and for interpretive material to promote the Aboriginal ownership of the 
Glen Helen Lodge and culture of the surrounding environment.<P>
<LI><B>NT Tourist Commission</B> for an awareness kit and visual aids to 
help indigenous people with potential tourism  projects, and for an 
indigenous tourism operators forum.<P>
<LI><B>Karijini Aboriginal Corporation</B> for quality publications and 
interpretive displays at the Karijini visitor centre, and to help Abstudy 
trainees attend a tourism training program.<P>
<LI><B>Kimberley Development Commission</B> for a product development 
assistance group to support Kimberley Aboriginal communities currently 
running or planning tourism enterprises.<P>
<LI><B>Kimberley Land Council Aboriginal Corporation</B> to establish a 
Kimberley Aboriginal tourism association.<P>
<LI><B>South Australian Tourism Commission</B> to develop joint venture 
guidelines for indigenous and non-indigenous partnerships.<P>

<LI><B>Queensland Tourist and Travel Corporation</B> to develop an 
approach to the Queensland tourist industry for funds to increase 
indigenous employment in tourism, and for a tourist agent in North 
America to provide sales and marketing support for a selection of 
Australian indigenous-owned tourism interests.
</UL>
<P>These projects will be independently evaluated, with the results fed 
into the final strategy before its release in June
 1997.
<P>
