<TITLE>On the shelf</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY background="background.GIF" link="#42426f" vlink="#8e2323"</BODY> 
<!-- Graphic Tag -->
<IMG WIDTH=453 HEIGHT=18 ALT="Number 9, September 1995" 
SRC="issuenumbergold.GIF"><H1>
On the shelf
</H1>
<H3>
<I>National Ecotourism Strategy </I>(reprint)
</H3>
<!-- Graphic Tag -->
<IMG WIDTH=87 HEIGHT=124 BORDER=1 hspace=10 ALT="book"ALIGN=left 
SRC="book1.GIF">Due to public demand, the National Ecotourism Strategy 
has been reprinted.
<P>First published in 1994, the strategy provides a broad direction for 
the future of
 ecotourism by identifying priority issues for its sustainable 
development and
 recommending approaches for addressing these issues.
<P>These publications are available from the information officer, 
Department of
 Tourism, on <NOBR>(06) 279 7162</NOBR> or <NOBR>008 804 465</NOBR> (toll 
free).
<BR clear=all>
<H3>
<I>Tourism and the Economy</I>, Number 1 1995
</H3>
<P><!-- Graphic Tag -->
<IMG WIDTH=86 HEIGHT=122  hspace=10 BORDER=1 ALT="book"ALIGN=left 
SRC="book2.GIF">This BTR report continues the review of overseas 
economies that are important
 sources of international visitor arrivals in Australia, with an 
examination of the
 Thai and Japanese economies.
<P>This edition also looks at international visitor expenditure (by 
State), the
 contribution of in-bound tourism to Australia's balance of payments, and

 estimates the Australian component of visitor expenditure in fully 
inclusive
 package tours.
<BR clear=all>
<H3>
<I>Domestic Tourism Monitor (DTM)</I>, December Quarter 1994
</H3>
<P><!-- Graphic Tag -->
<IMG WIDTH=86 HEIGHT=122 BORDER=1 hspace=10 ALT="book"ALIGN=left 
SRC="book3.GIF">This report, which provides early access to key 
statistics from the DTM, notes a
 3 per cent drop in the number of trips for the 12 months to December 
1994,
 with the December quarter dropping 7 per cent compared with trips over 
the
 same period in 1993.
<BR clear=all>
<H3>
<I>International Visitor Survey (IVS)</I>, December Quarter 1994
</H3>
<P><!-- Graphic Tag -->
<IMG WIDTH=87 HEIGHT=123 hspace=10 BORDER=1 ALT="book"ALIGN=left 
SRC="book4.GIF">This quarterly report now provides information on 
backpackers as well as giving
 early access to data on visitors and nights, expenditure, 
State/Territory of stay,
 transport and accommodation used.
<P>Backpacker tables for 1993 and 1994 provide backpacker visitor numbers 
and
 duration of stay by country, backpacker numbers and nights by State 
visited,
 and average backpacker expenditure by country of residence.
<P>Information on all BTR publications is available from the publications 
line, <NOBR>(06)
 279 7183.</NOBR><P>

