<IMG WIDTH=453 HEIGHT=18 ALT="Number 9, September 1995" 
SRC="issuenumbergold.GIF"></P><H1>
On the box
</H1>
<P>The last issue of <I>Talking Tourism</I> reported on a special series 
on rural tourism being produced for the Department of
 Tourism by <I>Cross Country</I>, one of Australia's leading television 
shows on rural issues.
<P>The first of the series went to air on Prime TV on 9 September and 
will run each weekend right through September
 and October. Check your local TV guide for details.
<P>Don't despair if you miss the series - it will be compiled into a 
video tape which will form part of a broader
 information kit, called <I>Cultivating Rural Tourism</I>, being 
developed for individuals and groups involved in, or who are
 interested in becoming involved in, the business of tourism. 
<P><I>Cultivating Rural Tourism</I> will be sold by the Australian 
Government Publishing Service (AGPS) for $19.95. You can
 order your copy by: <BR>
phone - Freecall <NOBR>132 447</NOBR> <BR>
fax (credit card or account customers only) - <NOBR>(06) 295 4888</NOBR> 
<BR>
mail -
 AGPS, GPO Box 84, Canberra ACT 2601 <BR>
or over the counter - at Commonwealth Government Bookshops in
 Townsville, Albury, Geelong, and all capital cities.<P>


