<TITLE>TOURISM ASSISTANCE GUIDE - FOREWORD</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/yellow_rock.gif"><H1><A NAME="RTFToC1">TOURISM ASSISTANCE GUIDE
</A></H1>
<P><B>Commonwealth Government </B></P>
<P><B>Programs and Initiatives for the</B></P>
<P><B>Tourism Industry</B></P>
<P><B></B></P>
<P><B>September 1994</B></P>
<P>Commonwealth of Australia 1994</P>
<P></P>
<P>ISBN 0 644 33474 6</P>
<P></P>
<P>This work is copyright.  Apart from any use as permitted under the
<I>Copyright Act 1968</I>, no part may be reproduced by any process
without prior written permission from the Commonwealth Department of
Tourism.</P>
<P></P>
<P>First printed September 1994.</P>
<P>Reprinted with minor corrections February 1995.</P>
<P></P>
<P>The information contained in the <I>Tourism Assistance Guide</I>
was compiled taking every effort to ensure accuracy and completeness.
However, Commonwealth and other government programs and initiatives and
contact phone numbers are subject to change, or otherwise altered, to
meet changing policy, business or community needs.</P>
<P></P>
<P>Users are therefore advised to contact the relevant agency and check
the accuracy and completeness of the information contained in the Guide.</P>
<P></P>
<P>The cover and text of the <I>Tourism Assistance Guide </I>are
printed on recycled, oxygen-bleached paper.</P>
<Pre>

</Pre>
<HR>
<H2><A NAME="RTFToC2">FORWARD</A></H2>
<P><IMG SRC="tagima2.gif" ALT="Michael Lee" ALIGN="LEFT">A key role for Government in the development of industry policy is to provide a business environment in which individual firms can build on their competitive advantages.  It is also essential that information on assistance be made widely available.</P>
<P></P>
<P>The tourism industry continues to be one of Australia's economic
success stories. It provides substantial employment and is one of our
leading export earners, offering numerous small business and investment
opportunities.</P>
<P></P>
<P>In recognition of  the importance of  the industry,  the
Commonwealth Government has expanded many of its initiatives to include
tourism and has also developed programs to meet the industry's specific
needs.</P>
<P></P>
<P>It is essential that the tourism industry is aware of these
programs, particularly in instances where the program's relevance may
not be immediately apparent.</P>
<P></P>
<P>This publication, the <I>Tourism Assistance Guide</I>, aims to
improve the dissemination of information to the industry on Commonwealth
initiatives and programs which may be of assistance, as well as
providing industry contacts, addresses and telephone numbers.</P>
<P></P>
<P>The <I>Tourism Assistance Guide</I> has been updated and expanded
in 1994 to ensure that the information is as current and reliable as
possible.</P>
<P></P>
<P>I trust that you will find the Guide of benefit to your business and
I would recommend that you take the time to familiarise yourself with
the range of Government initiatives and programs that impact on the
tourism industry.</P>
<P></P>
<P></P>
<P></P>
<P>MICHAEL LEE</P>
<P></P>
<P>Minister for Tourism</P>
<P></P></BODY></HTML>
